<h1 style="margin-bottom:0px;">VPC preparation</h1><div class="f14 metric" style="color:#656668;display:flex;"><img src="/assets/images/calendar.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="updateDate">&nbsp; Updated on 26/06/2019</span> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img src="/assets/images/updated.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="readTime">&nbsp; 1 minute to read</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><br><div class="mw-parser-output"><p>To deploy the suite on AWS, you must prepare a Virtual Private Cloud (VPC).&nbsp;
</p><p><b>Note:</b> If you are new to Amazon VPC, we recommend that you use the Amazon VPC wizard and select the&nbsp;VPC with a Single Public Subnet&nbsp;wizard. If you are familiar with Amazon VPC, you can create a VPC without using the VPC wizard. Make sure that your VPC has an Internet gateway attached. For more information about Amazon VPC, see&nbsp;<a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonVPC/latest/UserGuide/VPC_Introduction.html">https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonVPC/latest/UserGuide/VPC_Introduction.html</a>.
</p><p>The following procedure assumes that you will create a VPC with a single public subnet using the VPC wizard in the Amazon VPC console. 
</p><p>To create a VPC, follow these steps:
</p>
<ol>
<li>Go to Amazon VPC console at&nbsp;<a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://console.aws.amazon.com/vpc/home">https://console.aws.amazon.com/vpc/home</a>.</li>
<li>Click&nbsp;<b>Launch VPC Wizard</b> to create a VPC to host 3 public and 3 private subnets (Public Subnet 1-3, Private Subnet 1-3 in above architectural diagram).<br> <a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsBridge 2019.02VPC1.jpg" src="/mediawiki/images/d/d5/OpsBridge_2019.02VPC1.jpg" width="822" height="256" data-file-width="822" data-file-height="256"></a></li>
<li>Select the option "VPC with Single Public Subnet" and click <b>Select</b>.<br>
<a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsBridge2019.02VPC2.jpg" src="/mediawiki/images/a/a7/OpsBridge2019.02VPC2.jpg" width="699" height="279" data-file-width="699" data-file-height="279"></a></li>
<li>Configure the VPC with the following settings and click <b>Create VPC</b>.<br>
<a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsBridge2019.02VPC3.jpg" src="/mediawiki/images/c/c9/OpsBridge2019.02VPC3.jpg" width="717" height="505" data-file-width="717" data-file-height="505"></a></li></ol>
